      <guid>https://opguides.info/design/vbasics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;vegas-not-as-basics-of-art-and-design&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Vega&amp;rsquo;s Not-As-Basics of Art and Design&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#vegas-not-as-basics-of-art-and-design&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We have the basics that any art program will focus on - &lt;strong&gt;Lines, Shape, Form, Color, Space, Texture, Value&lt;/strong&gt; - and these are the standard starting topics for good reason. They&amp;rsquo;re tried and tested to make people better at art, and they apply to any piece. This is great, but I think there are a some things left out of this, I assume to make it more broadly applicable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
