    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://opguides.info/design/web/content/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://opguides.info/design/web/content/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;content-is-king&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Content is King&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#content-is-king&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;At the end of the day, you can make a cool looking fancy website, but you still have to have something to say, a story to tell, a tutorial, videos, something to play. &lt;em&gt;something&lt;/em&gt;. This isn&amp;rsquo;t a print book, you can come back and edit it later. The important thing is to just &lt;em&gt;make something&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It doesn&amp;rsquo;t have to be good at first, it just has to exist. You&amp;rsquo;ll get better with practice, regardless of what part you&amp;rsquo;re bad it - the writing, the presentation, whatever. Just put in a little time every day.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://opguides.info/design/web/cost/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://opguides.info/design/web/cost/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;cost&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Cost&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#cost&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A pretty big question you should ask right away is &amp;ldquo;How much does this cost?&amp;rdquo;, and you probably already know the answer.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It depends.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First thing you should worry about is the cost of hosting.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-hosting&#34;&gt;&#xA;  What Is Hosting?&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-hosting&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you want to, you &lt;em&gt;can&lt;/em&gt; run a web server off of your home internet connection. This has problems though:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;It means everyone will know your public IP and any attacks on your site will be attacks directly on your network&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This isn&amp;rsquo;t the end of the world, but it does mean you have to be reasonably smart and good about network security&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You can use something like &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cloudflare.com/plans/#overview&#34;&gt;Cloudflare&lt;/a&gt; to remedy this, but at that point, why?&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Most&lt;/em&gt; home internet connections in the US are asymmetric, with a lot more download speed than upload. If you get a small amount of traffic a day, this might be fine, but if you have a viral post it&amp;rsquo;s unlikely to be able to handle the traffic&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Most&lt;/em&gt; home internet providers charge for a static IP address (Often at about $5/mo)&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You &lt;em&gt;can&lt;/em&gt; get around this with something like dyn-DNS, but that&amp;rsquo;s weird.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Most&lt;/em&gt; home internet connections are less reliable. If uptime matters to you, it may not be the best call&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The hardware costs money. Even a Raspberry Pi isn&amp;rsquo;t free, and neither is the power to run it.&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Even a pi 3b+ will use ~$5 of electricity a year, and the cost of the pi is ~$40 not counting the power supply, case, SD card, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TL;DR:&lt;/strong&gt; economies of scale will hit you here, it&amp;rsquo;s cheaper, safer, and typically better for users if you host with either a &lt;strong&gt;V&lt;/strong&gt;irtual &lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;rivate &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;erver (VPS) or use a web hosting solution- either free or paid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://opguides.info/design/web/garden/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://opguides.info/design/web/garden/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;your-own-garden&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Your Own Garden&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#your-own-garden&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I just said you&amp;rsquo;d need to learn a bunch to do this, so, why bother?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Platforms like Facebook, Tumblr, etc. - Social Media - don&amp;rsquo;t let you customize the look of your page&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;‚Ä¶ and they track you&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;‚Ä¶ and they make the experience bad for those without accounts&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;‚Ä¶ and they can limit your speech, ban your account, etc.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Site builders (Squarespace, Wix, WordPress, etc.) tend to lead to cookie-cutter websites&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://opguides.info/design/web/jack/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://opguides.info/design/web/jack/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;jack-of-all-trades&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Jack of All Trades&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#jack-of-all-trades&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You probably noticed the gradient heading this section: that was my warning to you that you&amp;rsquo;re about to walk into something that requires an interesting mixture of design and engineering skills. Making a good website requires a fair understanding of computers, some basic programming skills, and a willingness to dive into some technical topics. There&amp;rsquo;s a good reason most blogging now happens on Medium or Tumblr and that social media has boomed: The barrier to entry is dramatically lower. There&amp;rsquo;s also good reasons to want to make your own website and have your own little digital garden.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
